TONIGHT! KAZBAH Benefit w ROB GARZA (Thievery Corporation) & JAMES TEEJ (My Favorite Robot)
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Video: http://bit.ly/BuildingTheKazbah The KAZBAH Fundraiser Main Room: ROB GARZA (Thievery Corporation) Hoj (All Day I Dream/ Listed) Mark Slee (House- Heads/ Listed) Papa Lu (Night Moves/ The Kazbah) The Loft: JAMES TEEJ (My Favorite Robot, Toronto) Chemical Ali (The Kazbah) Elz (The Kazbah) Visuals by allofitnow! 100% of the proceeds go to benefit the KAZBAH 2014 on the Playa! The Kazbah is a burning man sound camp and artist collective with an emphasis on healing. The Kazbah is based out of San Francisco and operating in Black Rock City and beyond. 2013 was our maiden voyage to The Playa and it was clear it we were onto something big. After several successful underground events, we are excited to bring you our first public event at none other than one of the premier night clubs in San Francisco, Public Works. Rob Garza- As one half of electronic music pioneers/producers Thievery Corporation, he has been at the forefront of music and has traveled the globe performing, remixing, djing, recording and composing. Since Garza’s recent relocation to San Francisco, he has begun a re-exploration of his love for electronic music and beats focusing on Nu-Disco, Cosmic Boogie while keeping very groove oriented and outer-national based rhythms. Recently he has been djing and remixing, taking things to an even more spaced out and trippy level. James Teej Bio James Teej is a 32 year old Canadian born electronic music artist, producer and DJ currently residing in Toronto, Canada. With a career that already spans over 15 years and with over 15 years of professional music training, James has been a die hard music enthusiast for all things electronic, and is fast becoming one of Canada’s rising influential stars in the global underground music scene. In 2008, James began releasing his innovative sound to the world on what has now become a long list of respected recording labels including: Rekids, My Favorite Robot Records, Rebirth Records, Supernature, We Play House, No.19 Music, Galaktika Records, Connect Four Records, and many more. Constantly pushing sonic boundaries, all the while exploring the deepest recesses of house and techno, James’ music has been enjoyed the world over. And with highly successful remixes for such artists as Trentemoller, Adultnapper, Toby Tobias, Kenny Glasgow (of Art Department), My Favorite Robot, Patrick Zigon, and more, James has also become a highly sought after remixer for labels all around the world. With track support from the worlds top DJs and producers, a list that already includes Laurent Garnier, Radio Slave, Carl Cox, Danny Tenaglia, Osunlade, Steve Lawler, Jamie Jones, Seth Troxler, Damian Lazarus, and many more, James is carving out his place in electronic music. With this amazing level of worldwide support, James looks to continue his journey of creating highly emotive music that will continue to touch people the world over, in clubs, on the radio, at home, across borders, and cultures.
Saturday, June 7, 2014, 6:30 AM - 12:30 PM

The Good Hurt @ Slim's! w/ Marcus Eaton + Dylan Cannon & The Wound Lickers
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Get tickets at http://www.slimstickets.com/events/157401/TheGoodHurt This show is ALL AGES - so all you under 21ers who can never come to our shows can finally enjoy a night with The Good Hurt. Also on this awesome bill - Marcus Eaton and Dylan Cannon and The Wound Lickers! You can hear tracks from The Good Hurt's debut release, You Are Here, at this link - http://music.goodhurtband.com The Good Hurt are Seattle based, yet their sound would lead a listener to believe they came from the same golden hills and sunny beaches of Southern California that churned out the likes of Weezer, Incubus, Sublime and The Red Hot Chili Peppers. As an entirely indie operation they have made impressive strides in their first two years as a band: landing their first showcase at SXSW this past March, recording a debut album funded entirely by their fans and touring coast to coast while selling out top venues in both Seattle and San Francisco. Their new album, You Are Here, out September 1st – reflects the growth they have made in their young life as a band. The opening track, “In Her Name” is a Chili Peppers-esque freight train demonstrating a new edgy direction and sense of confidence owned by the band juxtaposed neatly against the more laid back beach cruising anthem “It’s All True” riddled with three part vocal harmonies, airy guitars and a wickedly catchy chorus.
Saturday, September 10, 2011, 8:00 PM - 11:30 PM in PDT

Winter Shenanigans @ NIMBY
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Stop by NIMBY on Saturday December 12th and Sunday December 13th from 10am to 6pm for the season’s most spectacular event: WINTER SHENANIGANS @ NIMBY. You can view and purchase amazing works of art by the talented Makers at NIMBY, including pieces made from copper recovered from the burn site of the 2015 Temple of Promise. Be one of the first to play Gaige Qualmann’s rad new invention: Mini Bowling - one part bowling, one part mini-golf, and totally awesome. You... yes YOU! ... can be part of the Beta-Tester Bowling Team! Help Gaige find out if he actually made it certified Idiot Proof! Will Krampus make an appearance and eat some children? Only if there are kids here! (Hey, did I mention: KID FRIENDLY!) Will we get the giant tangle of Christmas lights untangled and put up by next weekend? Maybe.. where's the intern? One thing's for sure: we've got lots of things and much more stuff in the art gallery, and some of it can go home with you. 2015 ain’t over yet, kids, and we’re using every last day in December to send it off right. Featuring work from the talented: Clody Cates , Gaige Qualmann, Ken Griswa, Tiffany Barr, Cal Hicks, Nick Yeager, Tanis Cloutier, Trevor Wright, Jim Haynes, Michelle Bert , and more!

YAAAS! Dino Beats, Eats & Drinks
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Mamasaurus rises again! Within each of us remains the DNA of powerful creatures of yesterday: tyrannausarui, steggasauri, velociraptors, pterodactyls, and more. Science and art have found the most majestic creature, whose harmony with its environment was so complete, that all of us, its children, are alive today: Mamasaurus. Come shake your scaly dino tail with us as we celebrate the return of Big Mama to the playa! On Wednesday evening, as the sun sets over the western mountains, Mamasaurus will come alive, serving chicken fried dino, raptor rosé and prehistoric beats for all of her children. Let Mama take care of you in her jurassic oasis. Hang out in her plush dinosaur egg-filled belly or watch the sun set over Black Rock City from Mama's crow’s nest 25 feet above the playa. Shout YAAAS! as you boogie to some of the finest beats from around the world. Andy Warren (Believe You Me) https://soundcloud.com/andydwarren dot (MAMASAURUS) https://soundcloud.com/alittledot/jurassic-chillin Jackie House (Honey Soundsystem) https://soundcloud.com/jackie-house Mama’s excited we’re coming home. Come partake in her love! We are grateful and ready to share some mama love!
